{"article_id":"k5N1xDON0DxGY4NY","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"\" We are eternally grateful for the outcome here tonight .","depth":4},{"id":1,"text":"We have a suspect in custody , \"","depth":4},{"id":2,"text":"said Colonel Timothy Alben , commander of the State Police .","depth":4},{"id":3,"text":"\" We ' re so grateful to bring justice and closure to this case . \"","depth":4},{"id":4,"text":"Dzhokhar A. Tsarnaev of Cambridge was pulled from his hiding place in a boat","depth":4},{"id":5,"text":"parked behind a house on Franklin Street","depth":4},{"id":6,"text":"shortly before 8:45 p.m. in this community just outside Boston .","depth":3},{"id":7,"text":"WATERTOWN -","depth":4},{"id":8,"text":"Four days after two deadly explosions turned the finish line of the Boston Marathon into a scene of bloody chaos ,","depth":6},{"id":9,"text":"the 19-year-old college student","depth":9},{"id":10,"text":"believed to be responsible","depth":10},{"id":11,"text":"for placing the bombs","depth":10},{"id":12,"text":"was taken into custody tonight ,","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"bringing a sense of relief and justice to a shaken region .","depth":7},{"id":14,"text":"\" It ' s a night","depth":7},{"id":15,"text":"where I think","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"we ' re all going to rest easy , \"","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"Governor Deval Patrick said at a news conference in Watertown .","depth":6},{"id":18,"text":"With the second suspect in the case , Tsarnaev ' s brother , Tamerlan Tsarnaev , 26 , fatally shot in a gun battle with police early this morning ,","depth":7},{"id":19,"text":"Boston Police Commissioner Edward F. Davis said ,","depth":7},{"id":20,"text":"citizens \" can be confident that the threat has been removed . \"","depth":6},{"id":21,"text":"President Obama ,","depth":10},{"id":22,"text":"speaking at the White House tonight ,","depth":10},{"id":23,"text":"said ,","depth":9},{"id":24,"text":"\" We ' ve closed an important chapter in this tragedy. \"","depth":8},{"id":25,"text":"But he also said","depth":9},{"id":26,"text":"there were \" still many unanswered questions \"","depth":9},{"id":27,"text":"and said","depth":9},{"id":28,"text":"the FBI would thoroughly investigate .","depth":9},{"id":29,"text":"Dzohkhar Tsarnaev ,","depth":11},{"id":30,"text":"who exchanged gunfire with police from the boat ,","depth":11},{"id":31,"text":"was rushed to a local hospital ,","depth":11},{"id":32,"text":"where he was in serious condition ,","depth":11},{"id":33,"text":"Davis said .","depth":9},{"id":34,"text":"Police had approached him cautiously ,","depth":9},{"id":35,"text":"worried","depth":10},{"id":36,"text":"that he might be wearing a suicide bomb vest .","depth":10},{"id":37,"text":"\" We got him , \"","depth":9},{"id":38,"text":"Boston Mayor Thomas M. Menino tweeted immediately afterwards .","depth":9},{"id":39,"text":"He took to the police radio","depth":9},{"id":40,"text":"to thank officers personally ,","depth":10},{"id":41,"text":"telling them ,","depth":11},{"id":42,"text":"\" Good job , guys ! \"","depth":11},{"id":43,"text":"The apprehension of Tsarnaev was the latest stunning development in a day of mayhem","depth":5},{"id":44,"text":"that had shocked the city ,","depth":6},{"id":45,"text":"even as it was still reeling from Monday ' s Marathon attacks .","depth":6},{"id":46,"text":"An MIT police officer was killed , \" assassinated , \" Thursday night in Cambridge .","depth":4},{"id":47,"text":"Then a carjacking was reported .","depth":6},{"id":48,"text":"Officers pursued the car ,","depth":7},{"id":49,"text":"which turned out to contain the two Tsarnaevs ,","depth":8},{"id":50,"text":"who threw explosives at them .","depth":8},{"id":51,"text":"The elder brother was shot by police early Friday in a gun battle in Watertown ,","depth":7},{"id":52,"text":"in which","depth":9},{"id":53,"text":"fficials said","depth":9},{"id":54,"text":"they wielded improvised explosive devices and homemade grenades .","depth":8},{"id":55,"text":"Dzhokhan Tsarnaev was so desperate to escape","depth":8},{"id":56,"text":"he ran over his brother","depth":9},{"id":57,"text":"as he lay wounded .","depth":9},{"id":58,"text":"He later abandoned the car in Watertown","depth":8},{"id":59,"text":"and fled on foot ,","depth":9},{"id":60,"text":"disappearing from sight .","depth":9},{"id":61,"text":"Law enforcement mobilized ,","depth":7},{"id":62,"text":"sending legions of heavily-armed police officers","depth":8},{"id":63,"text":"to search a 20-block area of the community .","depth":8},{"id":64,"text":"At the same time , Governor Deval Patrick took an unprecedented security step ,","depth":8},{"id":65,"text":"asking people in Boston , Watertown , and several other nearby communities","depth":11},{"id":66,"text":"- totaling a million people -","depth":11},{"id":67,"text":"to \" shelter in place \" -","depth":10},{"id":68,"text":"stay at home behind locked doors","depth":10},{"id":69,"text":"and open up only to police officers with proper identification .","depth":10},{"id":70,"text":"Government and business offices closed","depth":9},{"id":71,"text":"as police cars zoomed on mysterious errands on deserted streets .","depth":9},{"id":72,"text":"The Red Sox and Bruins games were canceled , as well as the Big Apple Circus .","depth":9},{"id":73,"text":"Amtrak was shut down from Boston to Providence , as well as the MBTA , the Boston area ' s public transit system .","depth":10},{"id":74,"text":"The region came to a standstill .","depth":10},{"id":75,"text":"Then , at 6 p.m. , officials held another news conference","depth":9},{"id":76,"text":"to say","depth":11},{"id":77,"text":"that","depth":11},{"id":78,"text":"despite the massive manhunt ,","depth":11},{"id":79,"text":"they had come up empty .","depth":11},{"id":80,"text":"The suspect had slipped outside their perimeter .","depth":8},{"id":81,"text":"Officials said","depth":8},{"id":82,"text":"they remained determined to find him , however ,","depth":9},{"id":83,"text":"and that they believed","depth":10},{"id":84,"text":"he was somewhere still in Massachusetts .","depth":10},{"id":85,"text":"Patrick dropped his request","depth":8},{"id":86,"text":"for people to shelter in place","depth":8},{"id":87,"text":"and ordered the MBTA to resume service .","depth":7},{"id":88,"text":"The dramatic finale came","depth":7},{"id":89,"text":"less than an hour after the news conference was over .","depth":7},{"id":90,"text":"A resident of Watertown came out of his house","depth":9},{"id":91,"text":"and noticed blood on his boat","depth":10},{"id":92,"text":"and that the tarp","depth":12},{"id":93,"text":"covering it","depth":12},{"id":94,"text":"was ripped .","depth":11},{"id":95,"text":"He lifted the tarp","depth":10},{"id":96,"text":"and saw a bloody form .","depth":10},{"id":97,"text":"He called police ,","depth":12},{"id":98,"text":"who raced to the scene","depth":12},{"id":99,"text":"and exchanged gunfire with Tsarnaev ,","depth":11},{"id":100,"text":"said Davis , the Boston commissioner","depth":10},{"id":101,"text":"Police surrounded the boat","depth":10},{"id":102,"text":"and there was a standoff for about an hour and a half .","depth":10},{"id":103,"text":"A State Police helicopter peeked at him from above ,","depth":11},{"id":104,"text":"using a special infrared camera .","depth":11},{"id":105,"text":"Police deployed \" flash bang \" grenades","depth":12},{"id":106,"text":"to stun and distract him ,","depth":12},{"id":107,"text":"Davis said .","depth":11},{"id":108,"text":"Police were cautious in their approach ,","depth":10},{"id":109,"text":"concerned","depth":11},{"id":110,"text":"that Tsarnaev could be wearing a suicide bomb vest .","depth":11},{"id":111,"text":"A Globe photographer at the scene could hear police calling ,","depth":11},{"id":112,"text":"\" We know","depth":12},{"id":113,"text":"you ' re in there .","depth":13},{"id":114,"text":"Come out on your own terms .","depth":14},{"id":115,"text":"Come out with your hands up . \"","depth":14},{"id":116,"text":"An FBI hostage rescue team was eventually able to pull him out .","depth":10},{"id":117,"text":"In yet another twist in the story , New Bedford police said this evening","depth":8},{"id":118,"text":"that three people had been taken into custody in their city as part of the bombing investigation .","depth":8},{"id":119,"text":"New Bedford Police Lieutenant Robert Richard said","depth":8},{"id":120,"text":"his department assisted federal investigators","depth":9},{"id":121,"text":"in executing a search warrant at a home on Carriage Drive , about 10 minutes from the University of Massachusetts at Dartmouth ,","depth":10},{"id":122,"text":"where Tsarnaev was a student .","depth":10},{"id":123,"text":"MIT Police Officer Sean Collier , 26 , of Somerville ,","depth":9},{"id":124,"text":"who was fatally shot","depth":10},{"id":125,"text":"while sitting in his cruiser near Main and Vassar streets in Cambridge , in what Davis called an \" assassination , \"","depth":10},{"id":126,"text":"was remembered as a brave and devoted officer .","depth":8},{"id":127,"text":"MBTA Transit Police Officer Richard H. Donahue Jr. , 33 ,","depth":9},{"id":128,"text":"who was shot","depth":10},{"id":129,"text":"as officers pursued the Tsarnaevs into Watertown ,","depth":10},{"id":130,"text":"was in critical but stable condition at Mt . Auburn Hospital .","depth":8}],"relations":[{"parent":261,"left":137,"right":260,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":137,"left":134,"right":136,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":134,"left":132,"right":133,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":132,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"evaluation","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":133,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":136,"left":135,"right":6,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":135,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":260,"left":175,"right":259,"relation":"